request.description:
Scope Policy:
--------------
We can add a scope policy to multiple resource and methods. Resource and Method can have multiple scope policies.

Get the API details using our rest service and update the api with scope policy changes.

Adding scope policy to the API:
-----------------------------------
Like policies we have 'scopes' object to add the Scope Policy to an API. We can add 'n' number of Scope Policy to an API with unique name.

    "scopes": [
        {
            "name": "Pet Scope",
            "description": "",
            "policies": [
                "{{scopePolicyID}}"
            ]
        }
    ]


Adding scope policy at the Resource Level:
-------------------------------------------
Add Pet Scope to the Resource Level, if it is applied at the Resource level then it will be applicable to all the Methods under this Resource.

    "/pet": {
        "displayName": "/pet",
        "enabled": true,
        "scopes": [
            "Pet Scope"
        ],
        "get": {
            "scopes": [],
            "enabled": true,
            "requestBody": {
                "name": "requestBody",
                "content": {}
            },
            "responses": {},
            "mockedResponses": {},
            "mockedConditionsBasedCustomResponsesList": []
        }
    }


Adding scope policy at the Method Level:
------------------------------------------
Add scope to particular method.

    "/pet": {
        "displayName": "/pet",
        "enabled": true,
        "scopes": [],
        "get": {
            "scopes": [
            	"Pet Scope"
            ],
            "enabled": true,
            "requestBody": {
                "name": "requestBody",
                "content": {}
            },
            "responses": {},
            "mockedResponses": {},
            "mockedConditionsBasedCustomResponsesList": []
        }
    }

